TEST STATISTICI

#Carica le librerie necessarie
library(dplyr)
library(broom)
library(stats)
library(lme4)
## Caricamento del pacchetto richiesto: Matrix
library(broom)
library(kableExtra)
## 
## Caricamento pacchetto: 'kableExtra'
## Il seguente oggetto  mascherato da 'package:dplyr':
## 
##     group_rows
# Carica il df result_df salvato precedentemente
result_df <- read_csv("G:/Altri computer/Il_mio_computer/DOTTORATO/PROGETTI/FAGESOS_MONTE ARCOSU/SCRIPT_R/Treatment_Castanea/DATAFRAMES/result_df.csv")

# Elimina la colonna indesiderata $...1
result_df$...1 <- NULL

# Converti la colonna "plant" in caratteri (stringhe)
result_df$plant <- as.character(result_df$plant)

# Crea un nuovo dataframe uguale al precedente
df <- result_df

# Trasformazione della variabile dieta in fattore
df$treatment <- as.factor(df$treatment)
df$inoculum <- as.factor(df$inoculum)
# Applicazione del test di Shapiro-Wilk considerando entrambe le variabili
# Per ogni combinazione di "treatment" e "inoculum"

# Creazione di un elenco di tutte le combinazioni uniche di "treatment" e "inoculum"
combinations <- expand.grid(unique(df$treatment), unique(df$inoculum))

# Creazione di un dataframe per i risultati
shapiro_results <- data.frame(Combination = character(0), Variable = character(0), W_statistic = numeric(0), p_value = numeric(0))

# Iterazione attraverso le combinazioni
for (i in 1:nrow(combinations)) {
  treatment_level <- combinations[i, 1]
  inoculum_level <- combinations[i, 2]
  
  # Filtra i dati in base a "treatment" e "inoculum"
  subset_data <- df[df$treatment == treatment_level & df$inoculum == inoculum_level, ]
  
  # Iterazione attraverso tutte le colonne tranne le prime tre (plant, inoculum, treatment)
  for (var in colnames(subset_data)[4:length(colnames(subset_data))]) {
    shapiro_test_result <- shapiro.test(subset_data[[var]])
    
    # Aggiungi i risultati al dataframe
    shapiro_results <- rbind(shapiro_results, data.frame(Combination = paste("Treatment -", treatment_level, "| Inoculum -", inoculum_level),
                                               Variable = var,
                                               W_statistic = shapiro_test_result$statistic,
                                               p_value = shapiro_test_result$p.value))
  }
}

# Stampa la tabella con i risultati
print(shapiro_results)
##                               Combination   Variable W_statistic    p_value

## W1       Treatment - BV | Inoculum - AB21    avgDiam   0.9406590 0.67060148
## W2       Treatment - BV | Inoculum - AB21 rootVolume   0.8839026 0.32737113
## W3       Treatment - BV | Inoculum - AB21      forks   0.9844585 0.95696362
## W4       Treatment - BV | Inoculum - AB21  crossings   0.9402519 0.66771995
## W5       Treatment - BV | Inoculum - AB21  lenPerVol   0.9402519 0.66771972

# Creo un nuovo dataframe selezionando le colonne che mi servono pi length
df_lenght <- df[, c("plant", "inoculum", "treatment", "length")]
# Esegui il test ANOVA

model_length_aov <- aov(length ~ treatment * inoculum, data = df_lenght)

anova(model_length_aov)

##

# Calcola le medie dei livelli delle variabili.
means <- df %>% group_by(inoculum, treatment) %>%
  summarise(Mean = mean(length), 
            StdDev = sd(length),
            Count = n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'inoculum'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
# Calcola i limiti di confidenza (95%) per le medie.
means <- means %>% mutate(
  Lower = Mean - qt(0.975, Count-1) * (StdDev / sqrt(Count)),
  Upper = Mean + qt(0.975, Count-1) * (StdDev / sqrt(Count))
)

library(agricolae)
inoculum_comparison <- LSD.test(model_length_aov, "inoculum", group = TRUE)
treatment_comparison <- LSD.test(model_length_aov, "treatment", group = TRUE)

# Calcola le medie dei livelli delle variabili.
means <- df %>% group_by(inoculum, treatment) %>%
  summarise(Mean = mean(rootVolume), 
            StdDev = sd(rootVolume),
            Count = n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'inoculum'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
# Calcola i limiti di confidenza (95%) per le medie.
means <- means %>% mutate(
  Lower = Mean - qt(0.975, Count-1) * (StdDev / sqrt(Count)),
  Upper = Mean + qt(0.975, Count-1) * (StdDev / sqrt(Count))
)

)
